font-family: Arial;  font-size: small;  background: #ffffff;  color: #000000;
}
p {
margin-top: 0pt;  margin-bottom: 0pt;
}
--&gt;
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt;&quot;&gt;The Temple of the Ammonite idol Moloch which king Solomon built in the Valley of Gehena (I Kings: 11:7). &amp;#160;According to the Bible (I Kings 16:3; 21:6), the kings of Judah Ahaz and Manasseh &amp;#160;took part in the Moloch ritual by passing their sons in the fire. Below the sawing of the tree where the Prophet Isaiah hid by the slaves of the wicked king Manasseh, and Isaiah&apos;s sepulcher.&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
