--&gt;
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: 35.45pt;&quot;&gt;While the Alchemical papers, acquired by Keynes, were bequeathed by him to Cambridge upon his death in 1946, A.S. Yahuda bequeathed his papers upon his death in 1951 to the National Library of Israel in Jerusalem, along with many other important and beautiful manuscripts of all sorts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: 35.45pt;&quot;&gt;Newton&apos;s Theological Papers were bequeathed by A.S. Yahuda &amp;#160;to the library along with many other important Jewish, Muslim and Christian manuscripts (these include outstanding Muslim manuscripts &#8211; here is a short glimpse).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
